props.synopsis: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has denounced a suspicious blaze that tore through a Melbourne synagogue as a violent act of anti-Semitism aimed at creating fear in the community.

props.synopsis: Beds built in Melbourne using 100 per cent recycled plastic are now being trialled, and could have long-term impacts for plastic waste.

image.altText: A man pushes the button on a washing machine that's full of clothes

props.synopsis: Your washing machine may not use much energy, but how long will it last and can it be fixed easily if it breaks? Advocates say knowing the answers to those questions could help buyers see through deceptive marketing.

image.altText: A man holding 100 dollar bills in his hand

props.synopsis: The property investor and social media influencer regularly holds cash and prize giveaways on his social media to subscribed members of his rewards club.

image.altText: A potential logo for the Melbourne Gay Games

title.children: Organiser 'shattered' as Melbourne shelves bid for 2030 Gay Games

image.altText: A young woman holding a large stuffed toy looks at the camera with a neutral expression.

image.altText: A man wearing a hoodie on CCTV, smiling as he leans against a counter.

image.altText: A view from under a thermometer looking up towards the sun in a blue cloudy sky

image.altText: A man in a business shirt and suit jacket sits in a chair in an office, looking serious as he's interviewed for television.

image.altText: Jasprit Bumrah celebrates the wicket of Steve Smith
